807  INT *Tmp3; // [big_n]

1728  // if u is singular and v \in \la u \ra^\perp, then
1729  // \pho_{u,v}(x) :=
1730  // x + \beta(x,v) u - \beta(x,u) v - Q(v) \beta(x,u) u
1731  // is called the Siegel transform (see Taylor p. 148)

1733  // \beta is the corresponding bilinear form
